questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput microservice periodically fails to persist audit logs. The following code is used within a Spring Boot service: 

java
@Service
public class AuditLogger {
    @Transactional
    public void processAuditLogs(List<String> payloads) {
        payloads.forEach(this::internalPersist);
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void internalPersist(String data) {
        // Logic to save to database
    }
}

Despite `internalPersist` being marked as `REQUIRES_NEW`, if one record fails, the entire batch is rolled back because they are all running in the same transaction.
